  "title": "SPA THERAPIST",
  "description": "<p>A Spa Therapist</p><p>provides professional, high-quality wellness treatments—including massages, facials, and body treatments—to enhance guest relaxation and satisfaction</p><p>. Responsibilities include maintaining immaculate treatment rooms, performing expert services, and promoting spa products. Roles often require relevant certifications, experience, and the ability to work weekends.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities & Duties</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Treatments:</strong> Perform various massages (e.g., body, foot, Tui Na) and beauty treatments (facials, body scrubs) as per spa standards.</li><li><strong>Customer Service:</strong> Greet guests, deliver personalized, high-standard, and relaxing experiences, and handle inquiries professionally.</li><li><strong>Hygiene & Safety:</strong> Maintain cleanliness and tidiness of treatment rooms, equipment, and workstations throughout the shift.</li><li><strong>Sales & Promotion:</strong> Recommend and sell spa services and related retail products.</li><li><strong>Operational Support:</strong> Attend meetings, participate in training, and assist with inventory management. </li></ul><p><strong>Requirements & Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Skills:</strong> Proficiency in massage techniques, body treatments, and skincare.</li><li><strong>Experience:</strong> Previous experience in a spa, salon, or luxury hotel environment is often preferred.</li><li><strong>Certifications:</strong> Relevant certifications (e.g., ITEC, CIDESCO, CIBTAC, or local equivalents like WSQ) are frequently required.</li><li><strong>Attributes:</strong> Customer-oriented, positive, reliable, and capable of working in a team.</li><li><strong>Schedule:</strong> Flexibility to work weekends, evenings, and public holidays is common. </li></ul><p><strong>Job Opportunities & Environment</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Types:</strong> Full-time, part-time, and freelance positions </li><li><strong>Compensation:</strong> Often includes a competitive base salary with commission packages based on performance.</li></ul>",
